narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor define the topic of study?
comments: The topic's in the class were all very well defined and it was clear the instructor really cared that everyone in the class was on the same page

narratives.question_text: How clearly did the instructor outline the expectation for the course, classroom activity and homework?
comments: I was never confused about what was expected of me. When something was done wrong in the class/homework/test that teacher was always willing to go over it with you.

narratives.question_text: How well were individual class sessions prepared and presented?
comments: There was always a clear plan for what we were going to be covering that day.

narratives.question_text: How well did lectures fit within the boundaries of the course?
comments: Always on subject and to the point
would have loved the inclusion of more case studies as part of problem solving discussions or visual matter depicting completed projects.
Its a heavy workload but that is very fitting for the class.

narratives.question_text: How available was the instructor for help outside the classroom?
How useful were assignments in furthering an understanding of the topic?
comments: The problems in the assignments helped review what had been discussed in class, so was very helpful. Some problems felt repeatative though, and more variable situations for problems would be more interesting to solve.

narratives.question_text: If tests were given, how fairly did they measure knowledge gained?
comments: Some tests felt like a review of class work, though some of the problems were conceptual. The conceptual problems helped me more with gaining confidence about what I had learnt, rather than the problems involving more math which helped clear mathematical concepts through practise.

narratives.question_text: How useful was this course in preparing you for production work?
comments: Very useful in preparing me for production work. I feel that the second semester will really complete my confidence in applications.

narratives.question_text: How would you evaluate the instructor's knowledge of the material?
Please offer additional comments on such topics as: what worked best about the course, suggested improvements, class materials, etc.
comments: 1. More case study discussions 2. Separate booklet of appendices for the main course reference book.
